==================================================
MILESTONE 3 — local-agent MVP
==================================================

Context: Milestones 1 and 2 are complete.
Module: github.com/tuannm99/judge-loop (single go.mod, Go 1.25.1)
Layout: cmd/ for executables, internal/ for packages.

Current state of local-agent:
  cmd/local-agent/main.go   — stub only
  internal/timer/timer.go   — empty package
  internal/events/events.go — empty package
  internal/registry/        — empty package (Milestone 7)

==================================================
GOAL
==================================================

Implement a working local HTTP daemon (port 7070, localhost only) that:
  1. Serves as the single endpoint for the Neovim plugin
  2. Keeps an in-memory timer (works even when api-server is unreachable)
  3. Proxies submissions and progress queries to api-server
  4. Reports today's practice status (server + local fallback)
  5. Provides a sync stub (real sync is Milestone 7)

==================================================
CONSTRAINTS
==================================================

- Bind to 127.0.0.1:7070 only — never 0.0.0.0
- No CGO, no SQLite in Milestone 3
  Timer state is in-memory. Lost on restart — acceptable for MVP.
  SQLite persistence is a Milestone 7 concern.
- Best-effort server sync: timer start/stop attempts to notify api-server
  but never fails the local response if the server is unreachable.
- Submit requires api-server reachability (can't judge offline).
- Config is YAML file; env vars override. Both are optional (all have defaults).
- No new direct Go dependencies beyond what is already in go.mod
  (gin, uuid, pgx already present; yaml.v3 is already an indirect dep of gin).

==================================================
INTERNAL/TIMER DESIGN
==================================================

File: internal/timer/timer.go

In-memory timer for the active practice session.
Thread-safe via sync.Mutex.

Types:
  Entry{ID uuid.UUID, ProblemID *uuid.UUID, StartedAt time.Time}
  LocalTimer{mu sync.Mutex, active *Entry}

Methods:
  func NewLocalTimer() *LocalTimer
  func (t *LocalTimer) Start(problemID *uuid.UUID) Entry
    — stops any existing active entry before starting a new one
  func (t *LocalTimer) Stop() (Entry, bool)
    — returns the stopped entry and whether there was an active timer
  func (t *LocalTimer) Active() *Entry
    — returns nil if no active timer
  func (t *LocalTimer) ElapsedSecs() int
    — returns seconds since StartedAt, 0 if no active timer

