==================================================
CONFIG
==================================================

File: cmd/local-agent/config.go

Config struct:
  ServerURL string  // api-server base URL
  Port      int     // local listen port
  UserID    string  // hardcoded dev user UUID (no auth in v1)
  DataDir   string  // reserved for future SQLite / registry cache

Config file: ~/.config/judge-loop/agent.yaml
  server_url: http://localhost:8080
  port: 7070
  user_id: 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001
  data_dir: ~/.local/share/judge-loop

Env overrides (take precedence over YAML):
  JUDGE_SERVER_URL
  JUDGE_PORT
  JUDGE_USER_ID

LoadConfig():
  1. set defaults
  2. try to read ~/.config/judge-loop/agent.yaml; log warning if missing, don't error
  3. apply env overrides
  4. return Config

==================================================
APICLIENT DESIGN
==================================================

File: cmd/local-agent/apiclient.go

Wraps all api-server calls. Returns typed responses or errors.
Uses net/http with 3s timeout for status/timer calls, 10s for submit.

type APIClient struct {
    baseURL string
    userID  string
    http    *http.Client
}

Methods:
  NewAPIClient(serverURL, userID string) *APIClient

  ProgressToday(ctx) (*ProgressResponse, error)
    → GET {serverURL}/api/progress/today

  StartTimer(ctx, problemID string) error
    → POST {serverURL}/api/timers/start  body: {problem_id}

  StopTimer(ctx) error
    → POST {serverURL}/api/timers/stop   body: {}

  CurrentTimer(ctx) (*TimerResponse, error)
    → GET {serverURL}/api/timers/current

  Submit(ctx, req SubmitRequest) (*SubmitResponse, error)
    → POST {serverURL}/api/submissions

Response types (defined in apiclient.go):
  ProgressResponse{Date, Solved, Attempted, TimeSpentMinutes, Streak int}
  TimerResponse{Active bool, StartedAt *time.Time, ElapsedSeconds int, ProblemID *string}
  SubmitRequest{ProblemID, Language, Code, SessionID string}
  SubmitResponse{SubmissionID, Status string}

==================================================
ENDPOINTS
==================================================

GET /local/status/today
  Logic:
    → try ProgressToday (2s timeout)
    → if success: practiced = (Solved > 0 || local timer active)
    → if server unreachable: practiced = (local timer active)
    → return {practiced bool, solved_count int, active_timer bool, message string}

  Response:
    { "practiced": false, "solved_count": 0, "active_timer": false,
      "message": "No practice yet today. Start a session!" }
    { "practiced": true,  "solved_count": 1, "active_timer": false,
      "message": "Good work! 1 problem solved today." }

GET /local/timer/current
  Logic:
    → if local timer active: return local state (elapsed computed live)
    → else: try CurrentTimer from api-server; return result
  Response: { "active": bool, "elapsed_seconds": int, "started_at": time?, "problem_id": string? }

POST /local/timer/start
  Body: { "problem_id": "uuid or empty string" }
  Logic:
    → timer.Start(problemID)
    → goroutine: try client.StartTimer (best-effort, log error only)
  Response: { "id": uuid, "started_at": time }

POST /local/timer/stop
  Body: {}
  Logic:
    → entry, ok := timer.Stop()
    → if !ok: return { "active": false, "elapsed_seconds": 0 }
    → goroutine: try client.StopTimer (best-effort)
  Response: { "elapsed_seconds": int }

POST /local/submit
  Body: { "problem_id", "language", "code" }
  Logic:
    → build SubmitRequest
    → if local timer active: attach session context via X-Session-ID header
      (api-server will look this up — future; for now just pass session_id field)
    → client.Submit(ctx, req) — returns error if server unreachable
  Response: { "submission_id": uuid, "status": "pending" } or 502 on server error

POST /local/sync
  Body: {}
  Response: { "synced": false, "message": "registry sync not yet implemented (Milestone 7)" }

==================================================
SERVER SETUP
==================================================

File: cmd/local-agent/server.go

- gin.New() with Logger + Recovery middleware
- Listen on 127.0.0.1:{port} — NOT 0.0.0.0
- GET  /local/status/today
- GET  /local/timer/current
- POST /local/timer/start
- POST /local/timer/stop
- POST /local/submit
- POST /local/sync
- GET  /health → { "status": "ok" }

==================================================
INTERNAL/TIMER IMPLEMENTATION NOTES
==================================================

- Start() assigns a new uuid.New() to the entry
- Start() auto-stops any existing active timer (same as api-server behaviour)
- ElapsedSecs() uses time.Since(entry.StartedAt)
- All methods acquire the mutex; callers do not need to lock

